##"The 2020 Tokyo Olympics will go ahead as planned. "

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Nan Boyi, _ the_paper _ reporter

Tokyo 2020 Olympic and Paralympic Games will be held as scheduled, Chief Cabinet Secretary Yoshihide Suga said Tuesday.

The 2020 Tokyo Olympic and Paralympic Games will be held as scheduled, Yoshihide Suga said at a news conference Tuesday, Kyodo News Agency reported Thursday. He pointed out that the Japanese government will take the situation of the spread of the new crown pneumonia into consideration, in order to hold a safe conference for athletes and spectators, to advance the preparatory work.

Regarding the government's response to prevent the spread of the epidemic, Yoshihide Suga said the International Olympic Committee believed Japan was responding appropriately.

It is reported that the Tokyo Olympic Games is scheduled to open on July 24 this year, closing on August 9, the Paralympic Games will be held between August 25 to September 6.

As the number of people infected with COVID-19 in Japan continues to rise, there are concerns that the Tokyo Olympics could be affected by the outbreak. As of 9:00 AM local time on the 21st, there were 728 confirmed cases of new pneumonia in Japan, including 634 confirmed cases from the "Diamond Princess" cruise ship, including 2 deaths.

This issue is edited by Xing Tan
